annotationA: Methyl methanesulfonate sensitivity 4 is the non-catalytic subunit of the mus81-mms4 structure-selective endonuclease that functions in DNA repair
annotationB: Structure-specific endonuclease subunit SLX1 homolog; Catalytic subunit of a heterodimeric structure-specific endonuclease that resolves DNA secondary structures generated during DNA repair and recombination. Has endonuclease activity towards branched DNA substrates, introducing single-strand cuts in duplex DNA close to junctions with ss-DNA; Belongs to the SLX1 family
